---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import RetirementCountdownCalculator from '../components/RetirementCountdownCalculator.jsx';
---

<Layout
	title="Retirement Countdown Calculator — How Long Until You Retire? | Clockr"
	description="Calculate how long until you reach your retirement age. Countdown in years, months and days, with UK State Pension age as the default target."
	category="birthdays"
>
	<div class="rcc-page">
		<div class="rcc-header">
			<div class="rcc-eyebrow">
				<span class="rcc-eyebrow-square" aria-hidden="true"></span>
				AGE & BIRTHDAYS
			</div>
			<h1 class="rcc-title">
				<span class="rcc-gradient">Retirement Countdown</span><br />
				<span class="rcc-gradient">Calculator</span>
			</h1>
			<p class="rcc-subtitle">
				Find out exactly how long until you retire
			</p>
		</div>

		<RetirementCountdownCalculator client:load />

		<section class="rcc-how">
			<h2 class="rcc-section-title">How it works</h2>
			<div class="rcc-how-card">
				<p>
					The UK State Pension age — the age at which most people can start
					claiming the State Pension — has changed several times over recent
					decades. For many years it was 65 for men and 60 for women, before
					gradually equalising. It is currently 66 and rising to 67 for people
					born after certain dates. Further increases are planned, with State
					Pension age set to reach 68 for some cohorts between 2044 and 2046,
					though government policy can change. Clockr uses 67 as the default
					target because that is the current State Pension age for many people
					reaching retirement in the coming years.
				</p>
				<p>
					State Pension age is not the same as when you might personally choose
					to stop working. Many people retire earlier or later depending on
					workplace pensions, private savings, health, and personal plans. Some
					employers offer early retirement options; others continue working past
					State Pension age. This calculator lets you enter any retirement age
					so you can model a private pension target, an early retirement goal, or
					the State Pension age — whichever is most relevant to your planning.
				</p>
				<p>
					Enter your date of birth and a target retirement age, and Clockr
					calculates the calendar date on which you reach that age, then counts
					down the remaining years, months, and days from today. A progress bar
					shows how far through a simplified working life you are, using age 21
					as an assumed start point. Pension rules and ages can change — always
					check your exact State Pension age on the official GOV.UK website or
					with your pension provider before making decisions.
				</p>
			</div>
		</section>

		<section class="rcc-faq">
			<h2 class="rcc-section-title">Frequently asked questions</h2>
			<div class="rcc-faq-list">
				<details class="rcc-faq-item">
					<summary class="rcc-faq-question"
						>What is the UK State Pension age?</summary
					>
					<div class="rcc-faq-answer">
						<p>
							The UK State Pension age is the earliest age at which most people
							can start receiving the State Pension. It depends on your date of
							birth and has been rising gradually. For many people currently
							approaching retirement, it is 66 or 67. You can check your exact
							State Pension age on the official GOV.UK website using your date of
							birth.
						</p>
					</div>
				</details>

				<details class="rcc-faq-item">
					<summary class="rcc-faq-question"
						>Is the State Pension age changing in the future?</summary
					>
					<div class="rcc-faq-answer">
						<p>
							Yes. The State Pension age is scheduled to rise further, with 68
							planned for some birth cohorts between 2044 and 2046. However,
							government policy on pension ages can change, and past reviews have
							sometimes delayed or accelerated planned increases. Always check the
							current official guidance rather than relying on a fixed number.
						</p>
					</div>
				</details>

				<details class="rcc-faq-item">
					<summary class="rcc-faq-question"
						>Can I retire before my State Pension age?</summary
					>
					<div class="rcc-faq-answer">
						<p>
							Many people stop working before reaching State Pension age. Whether
							that is possible depends on your personal finances, workplace or
							private pension arrangements, and other savings — not on the State
							Pension age alone. This calculator can model any target age, so
							you can see how long until age 60, 65, or any other date you are
							planning towards.
						</p>
					</div>
				</details>

				<details class="rcc-faq-item">
					<summary class="rcc-faq-question"
						>How is my retirement date calculated?</summary
					>
					<div class="rcc-faq-answer">
						<p>
							Clockr adds your chosen retirement age in full years to your date
							of birth. For example, if you were born on 14 March 1973 and
							choose age 67, your retirement date is 14 March 2040. The
							countdown then measures the years, months, and days from today to
							that date, accounting for months of different lengths and leap
							years.
						</p>
					</div>
				</details>

				<details class="rcc-faq-item">
					<summary class="rcc-faq-question"
						>What&apos;s the difference between State Pension age and a private
						pension age?</summary
					>
					<div class="rcc-faq-answer">
						<p>
							State Pension age is set by the government and determines when you
							can claim the State Pension. A workplace or private pension may
							have a different &ldquo;normal retirement age&rdquo; or allow
							earlier access under specific rules — often from age 55, though
							rules vary by scheme and are subject to change. The two ages are
							independent; reaching one does not automatically mean you can access
							the other.
						</p>
					</div>
				</details>

				<details class="rcc-faq-item">
					<summary class="rcc-faq-question"
						>How do I check my exact State Pension age?</summary
					>
					<div class="rcc-faq-answer">
						<p>
							The most reliable way is to use the State Pension age checker on
							GOV.UK, which calculates your age based on your date of birth and
							current legislation. You can also check your State Pension forecast
							through the same service to see what you may be entitled to and
							when. Pension providers can give details for workplace and private
							schemes separately.
						</p>
					</div>
				</details>
			</div>
		</section>

		<div class="rcc-related">
			<h3 class="rcc-related-title">Related tools</h3>
			<div class="rcc-related-grid">
				<a href="/age-calculator" class="rcc-related-card"
					><span class="rcc-related-name">Age Calculator</span></a
				>
				<a href="/age-difference-calculator" class="rcc-related-card"
					><span class="rcc-related-name">Age Difference Calculator</span></a
				>
				<a href="/days-until-birthday" class="rcc-related-card"
					><span class="rcc-related-name">Days Until Birthday</span></a
				>
				<a href="/life-in-numbers" class="rcc-related-card"
					><span class="rcc-related-name">Your Life in Numbers</span></a
				>
			</div>
		</div>
	</div>
</Layout>

<style>
	.rcc-page {
		max-width: 800px;
		margin: 0 auto;
		padding: 60px 24px;
	}

	.rcc-header {
		text-align: center;
		margin-bottom: 32px;
	}

	.rcc-eyebrow {
		display: inline-flex;
		align-items: center;
		gap: 10px;
		font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;
		font-size: 12px;
		font-weight: 800;
		letter-spacing: 3px;
		text-transform: uppercase;
		color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.7);
		margin-bottom: 16px;
	}

	.rcc-eyebrow-square {
		width: 10px;
		height: 10px;
		border-radius: 3px;
		background: #8b5cf6;
		box-shadow: 0 0 18px rgba(139, 92, 246, 0.35);
	}

	.rcc-title {
		font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;
		font-size: 64px;
		font-weight: 900;
		letter-spacing: -3px;
		line-height: 1.05;
		margin-bottom: 16px;
	}

	.rcc-gradient {
		background: linear-gradient(135deg, #8b5cf6, #ec4899);
		-webkit-background-clip: text;
		-webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;
		background-clip: text;
	}

	.rcc-subtitle {
		font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;
		font-size: 16px;
		color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.5);
		line-height: 1.6;
		margin: 0;
	}

	:global(.rcc-tool) {
		margin-bottom: 56px;
	}

	:global(.rcc-card) {
		background: #0c0c0c;
		border: 1px solid rgba(139, 92, 246, 0.2);
		border-radius: 20px;
		padding: 24px;
		box-shadow: 0 0 40px rgba(139, 92, 246, 0.06);
		margin-bottom: 24px;
	}

	:global(.rcc-inputs) {
		display: flex;
		flex-direction: column;
		gap: 18px;
	}

	:global(.rcc-input-wrap) {
		display: flex;
		flex-direction: column;
		gap: 10px;
		align-items: stretch;
	}

	:global(.rcc-label) {
		font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;
		font-size: 14px;
		font-weight: 600;
		color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.6);
		letter-spacing: 0.5px;
		text-align: center;
	}

	:global(.rcc-input) {
		background: #0c0c0c;
		border: 1px solid rgba(139, 92, 246, 0.3);
		border-radius: 12px;
		padding: 16px 24px;
		font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;
		font-size: 24px;
		font-weight: 700;
		color: #ffffff;
		text-align: center;
		outline: none;
		transition: border-color 0.2s ease, box-shadow 0.2s ease;
		width: 100%;
		box-sizing: border-box;
	}

	:global(.rcc-input--number) {
		-moz-appearance: textfield;
	}

	:global(.rcc-input--number::-webkit-outer-spin-button),
	:global(.rcc-input--number::-webkit-inner-spin-button) {
		-webkit-appearance: none;
		margin: 0;
	}

	:global(.rcc-input:focus) {
		border-color: rgba(139, 92, 246, 0.8);
		box-shadow: 0 0 20px rgba(139, 92, 246, 0.15);
	}

	:global(.rcc-note) {
		font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;
		font-size: 13px;
		color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.55);
		line-height: 1.6;
		margin: 0;
		text-align: center;
		background: rgba(236, 72, 153, 0.06);
		border: 1px solid rgba(236, 72, 153, 0.18);
		border-radius: 12px;
		padding: 12px 14px;
	}

	:global(.rcc-presets) {
		margin-bottom: 24px;
	}

	:global(.rcc-presets-title) {
		font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;
		font-size: 16px;
		font-weight: 700;
		color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.85);
		text-align: center;
		margin: 0 0 12px;
	}

	:global(.rcc-presets-grid) {
		display: grid;
		grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr);
		gap: 10px;
	}

	:global(.rcc-preset) {
		border: 1px solid rgba(139, 92, 246, 0.22);
		background: rgba(139, 92, 246, 0.06);
		border-radius: 14px;
		padding: 14px 12px;
		font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;
		font-size: 14px;
		font-weight: 700;
		color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.75);
		cursor: pointer;
		transition: border-color 0.2s ease, background 0.2s ease;
	}

	:global(.rcc-preset:hover) {
		border-color: rgba(139, 92, 246, 0.45);
		background: rgba(139, 92, 246, 0.08);
	}

	:global(.rcc-results) {
		background: #0c0c0c;
		border: 1px solid rgba(139, 92, 246, 0.2);
		border-radius: 20px;
		padding: 32px 24px;
		box-shadow: 0 0 50px rgba(236, 72, 153, 0.06);
		text-align: center;
	}

	:global(.rcc-main) {
		margin-bottom: 24px;
	}

	:global(.rcc-main-heading) {
		font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;
		font-size: 32px;
		font-weight: 900;
		letter-spacing: -1.5px;
		line-height: 1.2;
		background: linear-gradient(135deg, #8b5cf6, #ec4899);
		-webkit-background-clip: text;
		-webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;
		background-clip: text;
		margin: 0;
	}

	:global(.rcc-countdown) {
		display: grid;
		grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
		gap: 12px;
		margin-bottom: 20px;
	}

	:global(.rcc-countdown-item) {
		background: rgba(139, 92, 246, 0.06);
		border: 1px solid rgba(139, 92, 246, 0.18);
		border-radius: 14px;
		padding: 18px 12px;
		display: flex;
		flex-direction: column;
		gap: 6px;
	}

	:global(.rcc-countdown-num) {
		font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;
		font-size: 36px;
		font-weight: 900;
		letter-spacing: -1px;
		background: linear-gradient(135deg, #8b5cf6, #ec4899);
		-webkit-background-clip: text;
		-webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;
		background-clip: text;
	}

	:global(.rcc-countdown-label) {
		font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;
		font-size: 11px;
		font-weight: 600;
		letter-spacing: 1px;
		text-transform: uppercase;
		color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.35);
	}

	:global(.rcc-total-days) {
		font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;
		font-size: 18px;
		color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.55);
		margin: 0 0 24px;
	}

	:global(.rcc-progress) {
		margin-bottom: 20px;
		text-align: left;
	}

	:global(.rcc-progress-top) {
		display: flex;
		justify-content: space-between;
		font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;
		font-size: 12px;
		color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.5);
		margin-bottom: 8px;
	}

	:global(.rcc-progress-track) {
		height: 10px;
		background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.08);
		border-radius: 999px;
		overflow: hidden;
		margin-bottom: 10px;
	}

	:global(.rcc-progress-fill) {
		height: 100%;
		width: 0%;
		background: linear-gradient(90deg, #8b5cf6, #ec4899);
		border-radius: 999px;
		transition: width 0.4s ease;
	}

	:global(.rcc-progress-note) {
		font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;
		font-size: 12px;
		color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.45);
		line-height: 1.6;
		margin: 0;
		text-align: center;
	}

	:global(.rcc-disclaimer) {
		background: rgba(236, 72, 153, 0.05);
		border-left: 3px solid #ec4899;
		border-radius: 0 12px 12px 0;
		padding: 14px 18px;
		font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;
		font-size: 14px;
		color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.6);
		line-height: 1.6;
		text-align: left;
	}

	.rcc-section-title {
		font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;
		font-size: 20px;
		font-weight: 700;
		color: #fff;
		margin-bottom: 16px;
	}

	.rcc-how {
		margin-bottom: 48px;
	}

	.rcc-how-card {
		background: #0c0c0c;
		border: 1px solid rgba(139, 92, 246, 0.15);
		border-radius: 14px;
		padding: 24px;
	}

	.rcc-how-card p {
		font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;
		font-size: 15px;
		color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.55);
		line-height: 1.7;
		margin: 0 0 16px;
	}

	.rcc-how-card p:last-child {
		margin-bottom: 0;
	}

	.rcc-faq {
		margin-bottom: 48px;
	}

	.rcc-faq-list {
		display: flex;
		flex-direction: column;
		gap: 8px;
	}

	.rcc-faq-item {
		background: #0c0c0c;
		border: 1px solid rgba(139, 92, 246, 0.15);
		border-radius: 14px;
		overflow: hidden;
	}

	.rcc-faq-question {
		font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;
		font-size: 15px;
		font-weight: 600;
		padding: 18px 24px;
		cursor: pointer;
		list-style: none;
		background: linear-gradient(135deg, #8b5cf6, #ec4899);
		-webkit-background-clip: text;
		-webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;
		background-clip: text;
	}

	.rcc-faq-question::-webkit-details-marker {
		display: none;
	}

	.rcc-faq-question::after {
		content: '+';
		float: right;
		font-size: 18px;
		font-weight: 700;
		background: linear-gradient(135deg, #8b5cf6, #ec4899);
		-webkit-background-clip: text;
		-webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;
		background-clip: text;
	}

	.rcc-faq-item[open] .rcc-faq-question::after {
		content: '−';
	}

	.rcc-faq-answer {
		padding: 0 24px 18px;
	}

	.rcc-faq-answer p {
		font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;
		font-size: 14px;
		color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.55);
		line-height: 1.7;
		margin: 0;
	}

	.rcc-related {
		border-top: 1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.06);
		padding-top: 40px;
	}

	.rcc-related-title {
		font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;
		font-size: 20px;
		font-weight: 700;
		color: #fff;
		margin-bottom: 16px;
	}

	.rcc-related-grid {
		display: grid;
		grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr);
		gap: 12px;
	}

	.rcc-related-card {
		background: #0c0c0c;
		border: 1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.06);
		border-radius: 12px;
		padding: 20px 16px;
		text-align: center;
		text-decoration: none;
		transition: border-color 0.2s ease;
	}

	.rcc-related-card:hover {
		border-color: rgba(139, 92, 246, 0.4);
	}

	.rcc-related-name {
		font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;
		font-size: 14px;
		font-weight: 600;
		background: linear-gradient(135deg, #8b5cf6, #ec4899);
		-webkit-background-clip: text;
		-webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;
		background-clip: text;
	}

	@media (max-width: 600px) {
		.rcc-title {
			font-size: 44px;
			letter-spacing: -2px;
		}

		:global(.rcc-main-heading) {
			font-size: 26px;
		}

		:global(.rcc-countdown) {
			grid-template-columns: 1fr;
		}

		:global(.rcc-presets-grid) {
			grid-template-columns: 1fr;
		}

		.rcc-related-grid {
			grid-template-columns: 1fr;
		}
	}
</style>
